200.description: A success response. A JSON response containing Expert Query's OpenAPI specification is returned.

externalDocs.description: Find out more about Expert Query

FileAttachmentCsv.description: Query output returned as a CSV (Comma-Separated Value) file attachment

FileAttachmentTsv.description: Query output returned as a TSV (Tab-Separated Value) file attachment

FileAttachmentXlsx.description: Query output returned as an XLSX (Microsoft Excel) file attachment

OutputFormat.description: This field is ignored in queries sent to '/count' endpoints

message.default: The current query exceeds the maximum query size. Please refine the search or visit the National Downloads page to download a compressed dataset.

apiKeyHeader.name: X-Api-Key
apiKeyHeader.description: The API key used to access EPA web service resources. The below default value key is used for testing purposes only. Web service consumers should obtain their own API key.

columnsParam.name: columns
columnsParam.description: The columns to return in the result set, and the order in which to return them.

documentNameParam.name: documentName
example: North Indpendent ph TMDL final ERRATA

objectIdParam.name: objectId
objectIdParam.description: The unique ID assigned to a data item under the current profile

outputFormatParam.name: format
outputFormatParam.description: The format in which data is returned. JSON data is returned inline, other types are returned as a file attachment.

reportingCycleParam.name: reportingCycle
reportingCycleParam.description: Filter the summary to a specific reporting cycle in terms of the four-digit year the reporting cycle ended (e.g., for the 4/2/2016  3/31/2018 reporting cycle, the four-digit reporting cycle is 2018). If left blank, the service will return the most recent cycle. If -1 is used, the service will return all reporting cycles.
